<br>
The only epic that is really worth it is the Bard one. All others, while they can be nice, are gravy, and not needed.  <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14384 >Crazney Octobre, Barbarian Warrior, XEV</a><BR>Officer of Hawkstone<BR>"True adventure is rarely fun while it is happening - only in the telling." <BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xathcarnage>Xath Carnage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/03 12:49:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4848.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epics are they worth it????</span><hr size=1> I got my epics a couple of months ago, and I like them better every day.  I am in a small guild, and won't be able to do big bosses for a long time still.  I was using SBoZand some offhander of about 1/2 ratio.  I expected to never use the blue sword.  I was wrong.  The two epics together easily outdamaged and outaggroed my previous combo, or even SboZ + red blade.  I am now begining to use the 2hs form more and more, as I duo with a botted cleric in PoI alot.  The 2hander lets me avoid reposte damage and thus I don't need clarity for the cleric.<br>
<br>
